events.description: First meet in 2019, Lets review our goals and events for 2019' Want to join our Core team? here's a chance!

events.name: Cloud Study Jam
events.description:
Want to get started on the Google Cloud, but
don't know where to begin? Join us for our
Cloud Study Jam!
Get official Google training, a $55+ value, free
of charge. Together we'll work through several
Google Cloud labs. You will get hands-on
experience with the Cloud Console, Kubernetes,
Security, IoT on Cloud, and Machine Learning.
Then after our live session, you will have free
access to more labs you can finish at home.
Complete all labs in the quest and earn a
Google-hosted badge for your online profile,
and additional 30 days access to the training
platform to compete any labs you want
Bring a laptop and charger (PC, Mac or
Chromebook)! The labs will run on all of the latest
versions of the popular browsers. For the best
experience, make sure your laptop has Firefox or
Chrome installed. Don’t forget your charger.

events.name: Cloud Study Jam Calabar Follow-Up

venue.name: LiftHub
venue.address_1: State housing lane, The street opposite Jasper. Walk inside
venue.address_2: and enter the gate opposite the water board sign post.

events.description:
Want to get started on the Google Cloud, but don't know where to begin? Join us for our Cloud Study Jam!
Get official Google training, a $55+ value, free of charge. Together we'll work through several Google Cloud labs. You will get hands-on experience with the Cloud Console, Kubernetes, Security, IoT on Cloud, and Machine Learning.
Then after our live session, you will have free access to more labs you can finish at home. Complete all labs in the quest and earn a Google-hosted badge for your online profile, and additional 30 days access to the training platform to compete any labs you want

Bring a laptop and charger (PC, Mac or Chromebook)! The labs will run on all of the latest versions of the popular browsers. For the best experience, make sure your laptop has Firefox or Chrome installed. Don’t forget your charger.

events.name: Kotlin Everywhere Calabar
events.description:
Kotlin/Everywhere is a series of community-driven events focussing on the potential of Kotlin on all platforms. We are aiming to help learn the essentials and best practices of using Kotlin everywhere, be it for Android, back-end, front-end and other platforms.

Whether you are a developer, a speaker, a Kotlin User Group, a Google Developer Group member or any other community leader join us. Anyone interested in learning Kotlin and its ecosystem, sharing knowledge, and hosting a Kotlin-focused event is welcome to attend.

If you are a developer wanting to learn more about Kotlin, or a speaker excited to share your Kotlin experience with others, you can join us.

venue.name: Calabar International Convention Centre (CICC)
venue.address_1: Summit Hills Development Area, Katsina Ala Calabar Road, Calabar

events.description:
GDG DevFest is our annual all-day developer conference that offers speaker sessions across multiple product areas, Codelabs, Hackathon and more!

But this time we are bringing the whole of the South-South regions to Calabar to experience this year's DevFest South-South Calabar.
We will for the 1st time ever bring this to the Calabar for people to engage and learn on a large scale with all of Google's South-South Tech head's and Gurus.

With viewing parties around the world, everyone can be a part of this interactive event that focuses on sharing ideas, experimenting and crafting beautiful experiences across devices.

events.name: FSI Hackathon Calabar - #PayAsYouKnow
events.description:
The Financial Services Innovators have a goal to make Nigeria a global leader in innovative technology-driven financial services, ensuring access to financial services and economic development in the new digital economy.
FSI is calling developers across the country who are interested in building innovative FinTech solutions using the Sandbox. The Sandbox is a safe and secure environment where innovators are excited to experiment with their FinTech solutions/ideas without regulatory inhibitions. Download the problem statement here..
https://sandboxapi.fsi.ng/assets/hackathon/fsi-hackathon-problem-statement.pdf

events.name: Firebase Study Jam Calabar
events.description:
With a Firebase Study Jam, your community members will learn capabilities of using Firebase for developing Web applications, share their experiences, and solve hands-on problems together. Firebase Study Jams are a great opportunity to bring members of your community together to learn this hot technology in person.

Who should attend?

Firebase Study Jam is best suited for:

1) those just getting started with developing web apps for desktop and mobile
2) those with programming experience on other mobile app frameworks
